This map was my second major project into mapping. My first is not finished and probably never will. 
This map consists of 6 main areas, the 4 warehouses, the house/office, and the crane.
Each area consists of camping and barricading spots suited to anyone's taste to zombie survival, as well as high spots as people like to climb away form the sprawl of zombies coming towards them. 
This map does not have any secrets as it annoys me to see people use them, i believe everyone should have a fair advantage in a zombie game.

Have fun with this map as much as i enjoyed making it, although some places i wish i could kill over and over again.

If anyone would like to use modify this map, please ask for vmf.

Credits to Mushroom for the basic base of the trucks.
(http://www.fpsbanana.com/prefabs/777)

Spent about 3 hours making this map.

Its a fairly large maze, with 60 spawn points, but caters to around 30.

Varying widths of corridors and several rooms allowing for barricading with vending machines. 

I wanted a claustrophobic feel to the map, with a sense of being lost, but not too lost.

Aware its not the best of maps, but should be a laugh.

Well. Not much I want to write about, but I think it has huge improvements over the previous version (zm_vehicelecnter_b2).

Mainly theres only minor changes to the map when it comes to new areas. I have used all the thinking for improving and twaking existing areas just because the map was large enought already.

It has some new stuff such as:

 - Smoke turrets @ the pipes

 - More small stuff to find/figure out

 - Tweaked spots

 - More realistic enviroment (now it also has 3D skybox)

 - New/tweaked details

well it has much more than those, but im not in the mood (morning >:f) to list out stuff. Its while a go I actually did the map, but now I polished final things and going to finally publish this new version..




EDIT 01.09.2009:


Some stuff I wanted to list before, but FPSB Edit page was broken etc.
So heres some thats in my mind atm:

 - Radar minimap

 - Reduced graveyard penaltytime

 - If stucked when teleported from graveyard, you will be automatically killed after a while.
(Just to prevent situations where 2 humans are stuck and zombies cant do nothing. Stucking can be avoided by not standing besides your teammate at the graveyard.)

 - Made human defensive breakables/barricades unbreakable by humas
(only zombies can break them, this was a major issue with the security barricade at the helpdesk)

 - Reduced the helpdesk hitpoints due to the change above

 - Made a escape tunnel at the helpdesk, so humans can get out of there if they  want

 - Made a escape tunnel out of office

 - Made the tires at the parking lot harder to defence: easier to jump in

 - Changed the position of the tires, so theres no direct view to spawn points
(With respawn this was sometimes too much for the zombies)

 - Lift cannot be blocked/stucked any way

 - Made the storage hall higher and added spot at the ceiling level
(screenshot)

 - Added lights at the pipes in the bottom spots where you cant see directly above
(These lights will be turned on only when theres some one camping, the lights will just tell that some one is right now there. So you 

dont have to go all the way down to check it out.)


And no this is not a full list. Just what popped in my mind right now and I'm not listing all the changes anyway. :P


So hope u guys have fun with it. o_O

So first of all this is my second beta which i made while ago. First beta were tested at public but I didint spread it anywhere cause I wanted to check how it plays and fix stuff.

Map has been made kinda low detailed to make it run fine with my current mapping skills. :D

Map has been also optimized so it did run perfectly with 32 players with respawn (all the time all players in battle). I had 60 - 120 fps all the time with my comp that arent so good. So for example most of zm maps has much lower fps with this comp.

Ppl did like it. Or I think so. When there was vote for changing/extending map allmost everyone did extend it 2 times row.

Map has also some "secrets" which arent so hard to find.

When u look at the pic #2 I think ure wondering that its annoying to fall from the pipes and die. But actually it teleports u to grave yard for 0 - 30 sec. So its not good idea to jump there in panic to get away from zombies cause zombies gets u for sure at gy (no camps and not so much space to run). Mmeh i think its better to become zombie than die? Em I wrong?

Hmmh I think I recommend 32 - 50 players for this map. It has 60 spawns.

About that it has mixed gameplay there is possiblity to camp normally, barricade, climb, hunt and so on.

I was going to release this map with my ZM MapPack 03 but I decided not to since it was such a big project for me. This map is really one of my favorites- ever. My friend ChaosFury, the maker of the other ZombieChaos maps, made the original months ago. It was, without a doubt, one of the best laid out maps I had ever played. After months of new releases I asked him if I could remake it. After a month and 1/2 I finally finished it and I consider it to be one of the best zombiemod maps out there.

I hope everyone enjoys this map, more than I already do. Special thanks to ChaosFury, whom without there would be no map. And also to the community at www.aceserv.net for beta testing it.

Enjoy.

I thought that by the time I had reached beta 4 of this map I should include bigger and better changes.

Map supports 40 players.

Changes/Fixes

-CUSTOM SKY (thanks Wormkiller)
-Made window in Chimney House smaller + altered props and light.
-Zombies can't enter windows, altered props and light.
-Shortened wooden beam in caves + narrowed doorways.
-Changed box stacking in caves (for the fourth time!).
-Only 2 windows are breakable in church now.
-Brush work changes to Sun House.
-Made area under stone stacks a bit smaller to help out no reload servers.

Hopefully next version will include more area portals and HDR. Thanks H2 for textures.

B3 isn't that big of a change but there are some fixes. I wish I could have gotten more feedback about the errors so I can make a better map.

CHANGELOG...
Map now supports 40 PLAYERS (use to support 36, NOT 64, sorry for misunderstanding).
Altered props in Chimney House.
Altered Church props, and ceiling.
Altered lights + walls in SunHouse.
Altered props in Ranch House.
Narrowed width of Cave doorways.
Added many atmosphere changes + addons.
Fixed sky problems.

Thanks H2 for making custom textures.
